channel.title: 459 or 474 Deob Editing Question
channel.description: I'm want to start with a 459 or 474 deob because that fact is the most of the bases that I download, won't process the upstairs to the slayer tower, or the upper part of the gnome agility course. I know I can go find a 459 or 474 deob, but how do I run it with a server as soon as I get it? If someone has a 459 or 474 deob, with a black source, it would be greatly appreciated if you could post links to it on here.

item.title: 459 or 474 Deob Editing Question
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

DivineSouls:

Running in high detail? I used to code a lot on xell-scape, this is where I first encountered the height problem. There wasn’t an option to go to high detail. I haven’t seen a high detail option. I may sound dumb here, could you tell me how to play in high detail?

Might be in the batch file to run the client.

item.title: 459 or 474 Deob Editing Question
item.dc:creator: @badger41 badger41
item.description:
@badger41 wrote:

Usually the problem with height levels is caused when the client is in low detail.

Make sure the client is in high detail and it should process all height levels.
